Pareto Front: BLEU Score vs Compression Ratio

In[]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.cm as cm

# Load data
data0 = pd.read_csv('single.csv')
data1 = pd.read_csv('group.csv')
data2 = pd.read_csv('stack1.csv')

# Add a new column with the file name
data0['Method'] = 'single'
data1['Method'] = 'group'
data2['Method'] = 'stack'

# Concatenate data
combined_data = pd.concat([data0, data1, data2], ignore_index=True)

# Combine data into a list
datas = [data0, data1, data2]

# Get a colormap with distinct colors for each dataset
colors = cm.get_cmap('viridis', len(datas))

# Extract unique tile sizes
tile_sizes = data0['Tile Size'].unique()


# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
for i, tile in enumerate(tile_sizes):
    for j, data in enumerate(datas):
        # Filter data based on the tile size
        filtered_data = data[data['Tile Size'] == tile]
        if j == 0:
            method ='Single'
        elif j == 1:
            method = 'Group'
        else:
            method = 'Stack'
        # Plot scatter plot
        plt.scatter(
            filtered_data['Compression Ratio'],
            filtered_data['BLEU Score'],
            s=100,  # Set marker size
            marker='o',  # Use markers cyclically if more tiles than markers
            color=colors(j),  # Use colors for each dataset
            alpha=0.5,
            label=f'{method} Tile Size {tile}'
        )


# Load data
combined_data = pd.concat([data0, data1, data2], ignore_index=True)

x = combined_data['Compression Ratio']
y = combined_data['BLEU Score']

# Sort data by BLEU descending, then by Compression Ratio ascending
pareto_data = combined_data.iloc[((y / x).argsort()).values[::-1]]

# Determine Pareto front: higher BLEU and higher Compression Ratio
pareto_points = [pareto_data.iloc[0]]


for _, row in pareto_data.iterrows():
    if row['BLEU Score'] > pareto_points[-1]['BLEU Score'] or \
        row['Compression Ratio'] > pareto_points[-1]['Compression Ratio']:
        pareto_points.append(row)

# Convert the list of rows back into a DataFrame
pareto_df = pd.DataFrame(pareto_points)

# Extract the coordinates of Pareto points
p_x = [p['Compression Ratio'] for p in pareto_points]
p_y = [p['BLEU Score'] for p in pareto_points]

# Plot Pareto front
plt.plot(p_x, p_y, marker='o', color = 'gray', linestyle= '--', linewidth = 3, alpha = 0.8, label=f'Pareto Front:\nBLEU Score vs Compression Ratio')

# Adding labels and title
plt.xlabel('Compression Ratio')
plt.ylabel('BLEU Score')
plt.xlim([0,8])
plt.title('Scatter Plot of BLEU Score vs Compression Ratio')
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left', borderaxespad=0.)
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Define BLEU Score threshold
bleu_threshold = 38

# Separate data by tile size
tile_sizes = data['Tile Size'].unique()

# Generate a colormap with Viridis
viridis = cm.get_cmap('viridis', len(tile_sizes))

# Initialize lists to store data points for plotting
tile_size_values = []
mse_values = []
bleu_values = []
memory_footprint_values = []
compression_ratio_values = []

# Iterate over each tile size
for i, tile_size in enumerate(tile_sizes):
    # Filter the subset based on the tile size and BLEU Score threshold
    subset = data[(data['Tile Size'] == tile_size) & (data['BLEU Score'] > bleu_threshold)]
    
    # Check if there is any data meeting the condition
    if not subset.empty:
        # Select the first entry that satisfies the BLEU threshold
        first_entry = subset.iloc[0]
        
        # Store values for plotting
        tile_size_values.append(tile_size)
        mse_values.append(first_entry['MSE'])
        bleu_values.append(first_entry['BLEU Score'])
        memory_footprint_values.append(first_entry['Memory Footprint (Bytes)'])
        compression_ratio_values.append(first_entry['Compression Ratio'])


# Set up the plots
plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))

# Colors for the bars using the Viridis colormap
colors = [viridis(i / len(tile_size_values)) for i in range(len(tile_size_values))]

# Plot MSE against Tile Size using a bar plot
plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
bars = plt.bar(tile_size_values, mse_values, color=colors, width=10)
plt.xlabel('Tile Size')
plt.ylabel('MSE')
plt.title('MSE vs Tile Size')
plt.grid(axis='y')

# Plot BLEU Score against Tile Size using a bar plot
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
bars = plt.bar(tile_size_values, bleu_values, color=colors, width=10)
plt.axhline(y=baseline_bleu, color='red', linestyle='--', label='BLEU Baseline')
plt.axhline(y=bleu_threshold, color='gray', linestyle='--', label='BLEU Threshold')
plt.xlabel('Tile Size')
plt.ylabel('BLEU Score')
plt.title('BLEU Score vs Tile Size')
plt.grid(axis='y')

# Plot Memory Footprint against Tile Size using a bar plot
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
bars = plt.bar(tile_size_values, memory_footprint_values, color=colors, width=10)
plt.xlabel('Tile Size')
plt.ylabel('Memory Footprint (Bytes)')
plt.title('Memory Footprint vs Tile Size')
plt.grid(axis='y')

# Plot Compression Ratio against Tile Size using a bar plot
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
bars = plt.bar(tile_size_values, compression_ratio_values, color=colors, width=10)
plt.axhline(y=1, color='gray', linestyle='--', label='Unit Compression Ratio')
plt.xlabel('Tile Size')
plt.ylabel('Compression Ratio')
plt.title('Compression Ratio vs Tile Size')
plt.grid(axis='y')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
